                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude drawing of a church (?), legend: ʾIyärusalem: fol. 2r.&#xD;
- Names of the relatives of the donor written in the upper margin or interlineally in small script: e.g., fols. 58ra, 89ra, 92ra-b, 113ra.&#xD;
- The word ʾǝgäle is marked above and below by thin lines: e.g., fols. 87va-b, 88ra-b, 88va-b, 90ra, 106vb.&#xD;
- Part of the line is taken up: fol. 65ra.&#xD;
- Omitted letters, words and passages are inserted interlineally or written in the margin on many fols.: e.g., fols. 30vb, 33vb, 37rb, 50va-b, 59ra-b, 74ra-b, 77ra, 96rb.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections marked by dashes above and below the words: fols. 41vb, 78rb.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: 33vb, 42va, 68va.&#xD;
- Erasures: 55rb, 78rb, 80rb, 146va.&#xD;
- Small script: 81r.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: e.g., fols. 36rb-37ra, 59ra-60ra, 64va-65ra.&#xD;
- Scribbles and doodles in the margins on many fols.: e.g., fols. 15v, 17r, 28r, 60r, 67v, 68r.</item>
